daries being drawn at the time between humans, “nearhumans,” and automata. As agency came to take on a more central place in the philosophical, moral, and legal traditions of the West, certain classes of people were excluded as less-than-human. Tracking the circulation of ideas across the Atlantic, Johnson tests those boundaries, revealing how they were constructed on largely gendered and racial foundations. In the process, he reanimates one of the most mysterious and yet foundational questions in trans-Atlantic thought: what is agency?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aAct (Philosophy) 0aAct (Philosophy). 0aAgent (Philosophy) 0aAgent (Philosophy). 0aAutomatism. 0aFree will and determinism. 0aHuman beings. 0aPhilosophical anthropology. 0aReligionxPhilosophy. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020 Englishz978311070477808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020z9783110704570oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073919040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226749860423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226749860/original  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070477-8  EBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-073919-0  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGFb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020